26/07/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Violent thunderstorms claimed four lives and caused vast damage in a farming area at the weekend, local media reported Sunday (25 July). 
A family of three died after being struck by lightning in the northwest town of Zagra. 
Lightning elsewhere in the north also killed a shepherd.
In other news, 22 Romanians were injured, two of them seriously, when the bus they were travelling in overturned in Hungary. 
In all, 37 people were aboard the bus, bound for Vienna. 
(AP, AFP - 25/07/04)
